Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a cream-coloured pottery storage-vessel, the exterior is covered with a self-slip, now much darkened, and remains of one line of black-painted demotic text.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Prof Walter B Emery
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393749) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393749)
